    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "To make this more robust, I think we should make `heartbeatChan` buffered (2 slots) and the send on the chan should select on both it and default (or ctx, in which case slots are optional).\r\n\r\nAlso, it might be good for the select on `heartbeatChan` to also select on context, just in case it's made into a deadline context at some point.\r\n\r\nAt least in this current incantation, it's possible for `hearbeatFn` to get stuck on the send due to race between checking `hbCtx.Err` and calling `cancel`.",
